# C++ and Vulkan Standards (Mobile-First)

Applies to `next/nlrc_vksplat/` only.

## Language and Platform

- Use C++17.
- Core library code is headless Vulkan. Do not add Win32, XCB, or other windowing APIs under `next/nlrc_vksplat/src/`.
- Keep Vulkan 1.2 as the baseline unless a documented target requires otherwise.

## Memory and Layout

- Host/device structs, push constants, and storage-buffer layouts must match shader layout exactly.
- Mirror shader layouts in C++ with `alignas()` and `static_assert(sizeof(...))`.
- Do not copy ref `PACK_STRUCT` packing or rely on implicit host packing.
- Push constants must stay at or below `kMaxPushConstantBytes` / 192 bytes.

## Vulkan Extensions

- Prefer core Vulkan 1.2 and broadly supported extensions.
- Desktop-only extensions such as `VK_EXT_subgroup_size_control` must be optional.
- Do not require subgroup-size control, float atomics, or shader int64 on OHOS unless a device/profile check proves support.

## Maleoon 910 Profile

Current `ohos-*` presets enable `NLRC_VKSPLAT_EMULATE_INT64=ON` only. They do not yet complete the Maleoon profile.

Required future Maleoon work:

- Compile and audit a 64-lane subgroup profile.
- Enable or replace f32 atomic paths when hardware lacks native float atomics.
- Keep subgroup-size-control disabled unless the device advertises it.
- Re-run radix/Morton and raster backward correctness tests on device before full training.

## Descriptor Model

- Descriptor set 0 uses sequential `VK_DESCRIPTOR_TYPE_STORAGE_BUFFER` bindings `0..N-1`.
- Per-kernel binding order comes from `rewrite-buffer-contract.mdc`; never infer it from struct member order.
- Push constants carry small per-dispatch values such as camera, step, learning rates, and image size.
- Do not introduce textures in the rewrite unless a later design explicitly changes the buffer-only contract.

## Abstractions

Reuse current rewrite abstractions: `HeadlessContext`, `StorageBuffer`, `ComputePipeline`, `StorageBindingList`, `DispatchShape`, and `PushConstantsView`.

Error handling follows `rewrite-error-handling.mdc`: use existing `check_vk`, not ref `_THROW_ERROR`.
